Sentencas: La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 (LSCF-GDC) composite cathodes with various weight ratios 90%, 70% and 50% of LSCF were prepared.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Mechanical properties, thermal expansion properties and electrical properties were measured for potential applications in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with graded cathodes.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LSCF and GDC as pure cathode and electrolyte materials were characterized as reference.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The absence of new phases as confirmed by X-ray diffraction (XRD) analysis demonstrated the excellent compatibility between the cathode and electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Mechanical properties such as hardness and fracture toughness were measured by the micro-indentation technique, while hardness and elastic modulus were measured by the nano-indentation technique.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion behavior was recorded by a dilatometer.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity was measured by the four probe DC method.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 50% LSCF GDC composite has the lowest relative density among all the samples.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficients (TECs) and electrical conductivity increased with addition of LSCF contents in the composite, while mechanical properties depended more on the density than the LSCF content.
Titulo: Characterization of La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2 composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
